  <front>
   <head>THOUGHTS on RETIREMENT.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">pining grief, and black despair,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hence from my breast, each anxious care,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And high ambition's idle claim,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With envy's, mean detested train;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">All vain desires, fly from my peaceful cell,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where sweet humility alone shall dwell.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Welcome sweet hope, and genial love,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Welcome, each blessing from above,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Peace and content, with heav'n-born rest,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Ah! welcome, to my placid breast.</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Such joys alone, as solitude impart,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shall ever occupy my tender heart.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Adieu! vain world, no more thy charms,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With fond desire my bosom warms,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For real bliss can only dwell,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Within the moss-grown rustic cell,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where peace, and innocence for ever reigns,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Free from those ills which idle pomp sustains.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
